#compdef webauthn_proxy
# ============================================================================
# webauthn_proxy - WebAuthn-enforcing reverse proxy (Go, Apache-2.0)
#
# Author : Quiq team
# Upstream: https://github.com/Quiq/webauthn_proxy
#
# webauthn_proxy is a reverse-proxy auth gateway that gates any
# downstream HTTP service behind a WebAuthn / FIDO2 / Passkey
# challenge. Operators provision usernames + credentials in a
# YAML config, deploy the proxy in front of the protected app
# (often via Kubernetes Ingress, Nginx auth_request, or Apache
# mod_auth_request), and on first access the user is redirected
# to the proxy's enrollment + login flow. After a successful
# WebAuthn assertion, the proxy stamps the authenticated user
# into an `X-Authenticated-User` header for the downstream app.
# Supports per-CIDR-network "trusted" exemptions, dynamic
# RP-origin enumeration, dual session timeouts (soft + hard),
# and configurable cookie scope.
#
# The WebAuthn lane is built on `github.com/go-webauthn/webauthn v0.15.0`
# (declared verbatim at upstream go.mod HEAD), the canonical Go
# WebAuthn server library originally extracted from Duo Labs'
# open-source webauthn-go and now community-maintained under the
# go-webauthn org (github.com/go-webauthn/webauthn, 1200+ stars).
# The library implements W3C WebAuthn Level 3 + CTAP 2.x: the
# `webauthn.New(config)` builder, the assertion + attestation
# ceremony state machines (`BeginRegistration` / `FinishRegistration`
# / `BeginLogin` / `FinishLogin`), the CBOR codec for authData +
# clientDataJSON, COSE algorithm support, resident credentials,
# user verification, and the FIDO MDS metadata-service
# certification chain.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 213 :: WEBAUTHN / FIDO2 / PASSKEY (W3C LVL 3 + CTAP 2.x)
# Round 1338 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 213
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : kanidm/webauthn-rs              [R1337 _defguard]
#   Go      : go-webauthn/webauthn            [R1338 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : MasterKale/SimpleWebAuthn       [R1339 closing]
#
# Both webauthn_proxy and defguard are real production
# Passkey gateways. The structural shape converges between the
# Rust + Go lanes because the spec dictates the byte layout -
# both libraries return CBOR-decoded authenticator data with
# the same field semantics, and a Rust frontend can verify a
# credential that a Go service registered (and vice versa)
# via the canonical CBOR + COSE wire format.
# ============================================================================

_webauthn_proxy() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '-log-level[logging level (default info)]:level:(trace debug info warn error fatal panic)' \
        '-generate-secret[generate a random cookie-session secret string]' \
        '-version[show version]' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]'
}

_webauthn_proxy "$@"
